This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=5035

Whitespace might be one of the most difficult programming languages to read. Therefor a syntax highlight for Vim proves extremely useful.

For more information on the Whitespace, see
http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace/
or
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whitespace_%28programming_language%29

It is important that you use Ctrl-L frequently, since Vim is not too happy about syntax'es that includes newlines.
